  "A ball is thrown from a cliff at height h = −16t² + 32t + 48 and a second ball is launched from the ground at h = −16t² + 64t. When are they at the same height?": "",
  "t = 1.5 seconds": "",
  "t = 3 seconds": "",
  "t = 2 seconds": "",
  "They are never at the same height": "",
  "Set equal: −16t² + 32t + 48 = −16t² + 64t. The −16t² terms cancel: 32t + 48 = 64t, so 48 = 32t, giving t = 1.5 seconds. In quadratic-quadratic systems, the squared terms sometimes cancel, leaving a linear equation.": "",
  "An architect designs two arches: y = −x² + 8x and y = −x² + 6x + 5. At what point(s) do the arches have the same height?": "",
  "(4, 16)": "",
  "(3, 15) and (1, 7)": "",
  "(2.5, 13.75)": "",
  "Set equal: −x² + 8x = −x² + 6x + 5. The −x² terms cancel: 8x = 6x + 5, so 2x = 5, giving x = 2.5. Then y = −(2.5)² + 8(2.5) = −6.25 + 20 = 13.75. The arches meet at (2.5, 13.75).": "",
  "A toy rocket follows h = −5t² + 20t and a drone hovers at h = 15. How many times does the rocket reach the drone's altitude?": "",
  "Once: at t = 2 seconds": "",
  "Twice: at t = 1 and t = 3 seconds": "",
  "Three times": "",
  "Never": "",
  "Set −5t² + 20t = 15: −5t² + 20t − 15 = 0, or t² − 4t + 3 = 0. Factor: (t − 1)(t − 3) = 0. The rocket is at height 15 at t = 1 second (going up) and t = 3 seconds (coming down).": "",
  "A roller coaster track follows y = x² − 2x + 1 and a catwalk follows y = x + 1. At which points does the catwalk cross the track?": "",
  "(2, 3) only": "",
  "(1, 2) only": "",
  "(0, 1) and (3, 4)": "",
  "Set x² − 2x + 1 = x + 1: x² − 3x = 0, so x(x − 3) = 0, giving x = 0 or x = 3. When x = 0: y = 1. When x = 3: y = 4. The catwalk crosses the track at (0, 1) and (3, 4).": "",
  "A student checks whether the line y = 4x − 7 intersects the parabola y = x² by examining the discriminant. What does the student find?": "",
  "D = 0; the line is tangent to the parabola": "",
  "D = −12; the line does not intersect the parabola": "",
  "D = 12; the line intersects at two points": "",
  "D = 44; the line crosses through the parabola": "",
  "Set x² = 4x − 7: x² − 4x + 7 = 0. D = (−4)² − 4(1)(7) = 16 − 28 = −12. Since D < 0, the line does not intersect the parabola. The line passes entirely below the vertex of y = x².": "",
  "A park ranger tracks a bird flying along y = 2x − 2 and a hillside shaped like y = x² − 4x + 7. Does the bird's path intersect the hillside?": "",
  "D = 0; the path is tangent to the hillside at exactly one point": "",
  "D < 0; the path does not intersect the hillside": "",
  "The path intersects at three points": "",
  "D > 0; the path crosses the hillside at two points": "",
  "Set x² − 4x + 7 = 2x − 2: x² − 6x + 9 = 0. D = (−6)² − 4(1)(9) = 36 − 36 = 0. Since D = 0, the bird's path is tangent to the hillside, touching it at exactly one point: x = 3, y = 2(3) − 2 = 4, so the point is (3, 4).": ""
